<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE6FFD9FF71F8E0FC1EF83A" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71F8E0FDC9F8E2" blockId="14.[151,1436,1806,1941]" box="[151,564,1842,1869]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FF79F8E0FF14F8E3" box="[159,233,1842,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="60.[151,250,1932,1956]" captionText="FIGURE 7. Neotropical Eudocima and Ferenta adults (dorsal aspect)." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 7</figureCitation>
: K–L, 18: E, 23: K, 90: B–C)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71F884FC1EF83A" blockId="14.[151,1436,1806,1941]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
This species is separated from similar 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FDA0F885FD26F8DE" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[582,731,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorans">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FDA0F885FD26F8DE" box="[582,731,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. memorans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FCF7F885FC70F8DE" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[785,909,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguina">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FCF7F885FC70F8DE" box="[785,909,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. anguina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as described above. 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB90F884FA9CF8DE" authorityName="Phalaena" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[1142,1377,1878,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="collusoria">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FB90F884FA9CF8DE" box="[1142,1377,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Eudocima collusoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an uncommon species reported from Columbia east to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FD3CF8A8FCC4F83A" box="[730,825,1914,1940]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FC96F8A8FC22F83A" box="[880,991,1914,1940]" name="Suriname" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Suriname</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
